by letting you in.

08:29.460 --> 08:31.950
Which means I do not want you

08:31.960 --> 08:33.919
distracting Damon from his studies.

08:33.940 --> 08:36.360
If you plan on living under my roof,

08:36.470 --> 08:38.260
I expect you to keep him on track.

08:38.280 --> 08:40.520
- I promise, Blanca.
- Good.

08:41.440 --> 08:43.679
And you can call me Mother.

08:45.080 --> 08:46.340
Cheers.

08:47.040 --> 08:48.280
Cheers.

08:48.380 --> 08:49.380
Cheers, Mother.

08:49.480 --> 08:51.180
Ooh, I like the ring of that.

10:10.060 --> 10:11.290
Costas.

10:11.360 --> 10:12.940
Is this your lunch?

10:14.620 --> 10:16.430
It must be Maryanne on duty.

10:16.530 --> 10:18.200
She never brings it in.

10:48.040 --> 10:49.540
It's Christmas.

10:50.120 --> 10:51.540
I'm the prince.

10:53.540 --> 10:55.660
Dance with me, Clara.

10:58.880 --> 11:00.520
Tony, you need to get back into bed.

11:00.540 --> 11:01.880
Get away!

11:02.940 --> 11:05.020
- You're ruining it.
- Nurse!

11:05.040 --> 11:06.350
Nurse!

11:06.450 --> 11:07.720
Nurse!

11:16.060 --> 11:18.530
She didn't even give you a fork
to eat this fucking meal with.

11:18.630 --> 11:20.179
- I'm not even hungry.
- Bullshit.

11:20.180 --> 11:21.900
You have to eat something.

11:21.920 --> 11:22.960
Get your strength back.

11:23.740 --> 11:25.400
Don't look at me like that.

11:25.500 --> 11:27.240
You have pneumonia.

11:27.700 --> 11:29.040
I've seen people

11:29.860 --> 11:32.240
walk out of this hospital

11:32.270 --> 11:34.720
who were much worse than that.

11:35.320 --> 11:37.560
We got Christmas plans, baby.

11:38.800 --> 11:40.860
Go see the windows on Fifth,

11:41.700 --> 11:44.460
take a carriage ride
through Central Park,

11:45.320 --> 11:47.139
go see The Nutcracker.

11:50.940 --> 11:52.360
When did you get here?

11:53.080 --> 11:55.160
What was I doing out of bed?

11:57.330 --> 11:59.180
You were dancing.

12:00.600 --> 12:03.120
You've always been my most brilliant,

12:03.920 --> 12:05.620
dedicated student.

12:06.720 --> 12:09.080
You were dancing, my darling.

12:22.540 --> 12:25.290
I can't believe I'm gonna spend
my last Christmas in here.

12:31.530 --> 12:33.370
This is incredible.

12:33.470 --> 12:36.139
I ain't never met anyone
who was a real genius,

12:36.140 --> 12:38.560
but you have the gift.

12:39.310 --> 12:41.379
You need to make a New
Year's resolution, Pray Tell.

12:41.380 --> 12:42.410
Elevate your game.

12:42.510 --> 12:44.960
Get your designs on a real runway.

12:45.020 --> 12:47.960
A happy man knows his place.

12:48.060 --> 12:50.180
Who ever got anywhere
by knowing their place?

12:50.200 --> 12:52.430
A man who knows his place
might as well be a dead man.

12:52.450 --> 12:54.336
A resolution ain't nothing
without a friend to kick

12:54.360 --> 12:55.856
your ass to make sure you stick to it.

12:55.880 --> 12:58.819
No point in me fighting with you.

12:58.820 --> 12:59.840
I know.

12:59.920 --> 13:01.490
So shut up and finish pinning.

13:01.600 --> 13:03.979
I'm gonna melt the Snow Ball
with this piece of finery.

13:03.980 --> 13:06.080
Send Elektra limping into the new year.

13:07.840 --> 13:09.740
What you doing for Christmas Day?

13:09.820 --> 13:12.440
Nothing. I'll probably go to the movies.

13:12.540 --> 13:14.500
They have discount matinees.

13:15.100 --> 13:17.340
Theater's all quiet and empty.

13:17.450 --> 13:18.776
Well, what about that cute
guy you've been seeing

13:18.800 --> 13:20.100
that works for the city?

13:20.920 --> 13:24.480
He... is at Roosevelt Hospital.

13:24.590 --> 13:26.540
- What?
- Yeah.

13:28.200 --> 13:30.840
You two was out dancing at
Escuelita's just last month.

13:30.860 --> 13:32.000
Yes.

13:33.100 --> 13:34.460
How bad?

13:38.330 --> 13:40.370
Pneumonia... We don't need to talk about

13:40.470 --> 13:42.240
- this right now.
- What?

13:57.520 --> 14:00.099
You think this is the first
time since I've been diagnosed

14:00.100 --> 14:02.940
that I had to talk about
somebody dying of this plague?

14:04.530 --> 14:06.620
Don't you dare treat me as delicate.

14:07.380 --> 14:08.960
The worst part is...

14:10.620 --> 14:12.760
that I'm used to it by now.

14:14.600 --> 14:17.680
You know how many boyfriends
I've seen go in there

14:18.140 --> 14:20.100
over the last four years?

14:21.340 --> 14:23.920
How are we supposed to get
invested in someone...

14:25.450 --> 14:28.380
if they can be gone a week later?

14:29.520 --> 14:32.390
As if this life wasn't hard enough.

14:38.700 --> 14:40.130
Oh, my God...

14:46.470 --> 14:48.140
Do your kids know you're positive?

14:48.220 --> 14:49.980
Now, what good would that do?

14:51.020 --> 14:55.080
I'm trying to build something
that lasts beyond me.

14:56.720 --> 14:58.419
And none of them are gonna commit

14:58.420 --> 15:00.420
to what I need them to do

15:00.840 --> 15:02.960
